{"blocks":[{"key":"c4okb","text":"Open the folder of segmented images and the Google Drive preference table side by side for inspection. Change the value in a cell to 0 if the corresponding body part is not ideal (biased) for further analysis, e.g., a wing is significantly damaged, an antenna is broken, etc. The terms \"left\" and \"right\" (i.e. left fore/hindwing, right fore/hindwing) as used in the table are all with respect to the dorsal image; 'right' wing pieces will appear on the left side of ventral segmentation images and 'left' wing pieces on the ventral right side. Thus, it may be easier to rely on the color codes in spreadsheet's columns to remind yourself which wing piece is 'left' or 'right.'","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"brs9b","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"58cgn","text":"   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"4rbr5","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"","data":{"guid":"AC7060401F8511EC855CF7C2A4BEDDAC","height":269,"id":320549,"is_video":false,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"1ou99","text":"Screenshot showing a divided desktop workspace with two side-by-side windows: one with segmented images in Adobe bridge (left) and another with the corresponding preference table in Google spreadsheet format (right).","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}},"mime":"image/png","original_name":"image.png","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/j3bhbctwp.jpg","source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/j3bfbctwp.jpg","type":1,"webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/j3bgbctwp.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/j3bebctwp.webp","width":550}}}}

Setting a reflectance threshold that is too high will wipe all apparent UV signal from the data. On the other hand, 940nm band reflectance is normally very high. A higher reflectance threshold will be ideal to capture the variability in this data which would otherwise be 'oversaturated' at a lower value of ref_threshold) Running multispectral analysis with multiple thresholds will allow the user to pinpoint which sets of data/threshold parameters to use for each wavelength band (i.e., the ones that yield the highest signal-to-noise ratio).Sets of thresholds customarily run are {0.01, 0.02, 0.05, 0.1, 0.2, 0.5).
